- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new language model that improves language modeling performance. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses knowledge graph relations to parameterize the joint distribution over words and entities, which is a common technique in AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new model that learns to predict appropriate relations in context. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also possible as the paper discusses the ability of the proposed model to annotate the posterior probability of entity spans for a given text. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses knowledge graph relations, which are commonly used in database systems.
